args:
Jeanne d'Arc is apathetic to Dragonyule until
Mym gives her a dress. When she puts it on,
she finally comes to understand the excitement
of the season, at which point she promises to
protect the holiday from any and all fiends.
Preparations are proceeding smoothly for those\nentrusted with the task of playing Saint Starfall.\nSome time later, Mym and Elisanne...
My darling will hold a Dragonyule party!\nAh, but it is such a lovely idea.\nDon't you agree, Elisanne?
His Majesty is ever full of wonderful ideas.
Transcending the barrier between\ncultures while sharing time together?\nIt's so utterly romantic I could die!
If only he'd show such audacity in\nour relationship...
My apologies for interrupting.\nMight I have a moment?
Oh, Jeanne d'Arc! Have you come to\nmingle in our little romance as well?
No. I've learned something about the\nfiends that attacked the village, and have\ncome to make my report on the matter.
Bah! Put aside such concerns and have\na little fun with us for once. It is the\nDragonyule season, after all!
While it's true that Dragonyule is the topic\ndu jour in the castle, it is a human affair.
Such things have little to do with\ndragons like ourselves, no?
My sweet darling is working his tush off\nso that species other than humans might\nenjoy themselves equally well.
If I may, Jeanne, you say you've learned\nsomething about the fiends?

Indeed I have. A number of eyewitness
accounts speak of a treant that has
bedecked its halls, so to speak,
with fanciful Dragonyule decor.
Why would a fiend decorate itself?
It seems to be something of a showboat.
It has, on past occasions, stolen village\ndecorations, laid waste to flower beds\nin the nearby forest, and so forth.
It has apparently made a habit of stealing\nbeautiful things with which to adorn itself.
I'm in agreement. Regardless, it looks as\nthough this treant leads the fiend horde.

I could possibly overlook a sad, pathetic
creature that only stole material things,
but this fiend is stealing the happiness
of the people as well!
Indeed. I will continue to investigate this\nmatter and report back if I learn anything\nof interest.
Why are you LIKE this, Jeanne d'Arc?!

Oh, don't you play dumb with me, girl!
Even the fiends are adorning themselves
in glimmering splendor and making merry,
but YOU still refuse to even consider it!
And what exactly would you have me do?
Oh ho ho! I'm glad you asked; it's time to\ninject a little excitement into things!
Just what is she up to?
So, blah blah blah blah, the situation\ndemands a cute dress for Jeanne.\nCan you help, Cleo?
Ah, I see. I shall start at once.
I'm sorry. You want me to wear...a dress?
Silence! 'Tis the season for such things.\nEven the fiends are doing it.
I cannot simply stand by while a beautiful\nmaiden does nothing but fight without\neven TRYING to be fashion forward.
I'll help you undergo a magnificent\ntransformation that gets your blood\npumping! ...Isn't that right, Cleo?
In the name of Saint Starfall,\nI shall create the grandest of outfits.
Ah, but first, I need to discuss something\nwith you.
YOU? Want something from ME?\nWell, THIS is unusual. By all means.
It's actually about a gift for\n{player_name}. You see...
Here you are, Jeanne. One dress.

By combining my dynamic fashion sense
with Cleo's raw sewing skill, we've
created a dress guaranteed to make
people's socks roll up and down!
Now hurry up and try it on!\nC'moooon! Gogogogo!
Well, since you went to all the trouble...
Hoo-ee! Somebody grab marshmallows,\n'cause this lady is on FIRE!
The dress looks lovely on you, Jeanne.
Well? How does it feel, princess?
Embarrassingthough not altogether\nunpleasant. I think my heart is...racing.
Did you expect anything less?\nThis is a special occasion!
And it is our duty to look our best on\nsaid occasions.
So you see? Dragon, sylvan, or human\nwe can all have fun on this day.
I feel as though I understand what you\nmean a bit better when I wear this dress.\nThank you both.
Everyone, this is bad! Fiends are here,\nand they're coming after the Yuletree!
I won't let fiends ruin a romantic night\nbetween me and my darling!
Is that honestly your biggest priority...?\nRegardlesslet's go help out!
We just created a happy mood here,\nand I'm not about to see it ruined!
Thanks to this dress, I feel I can\nfinally understand that mentality!
Which is why I'm going to protect\nDragonyule with all my strength!
